caption.paragraph:
Figure 8.

Leviana dimidiata

comb. nov., female (
A, B, F
QM S67628; 
C-E
QM S25402). 
A.
Habitus, dorsal view; 
B.
Habitus, ventral view; 
C.
Epigyne, ventral view; 
D.
Epigyne, lateral view; 
E.
Epigyne, posterior view; 
F.
Epigyne, ventral view (scape broken off). Scale bars: 2 mm (
A, B
); 0.2 mm (
C, D
). Arrow in (
A
) points to diagnostic character distinguishing 

L. dimidiata

comb. nov. and 

L. folium

sp. nov.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Epigyne
(Fig. 
8C-F
) ovoid wider than long, atrium bulging; central division broadly oval with narrow base; scape with almost parallel lateral border, almost translucent; often broken off anteriorly; spermathecae ovoid, almost touching centrally; fertilization duct very slightly curved and attaching laterally at atrium (Fig. 
6A
).

Eastern Australia from far north Queensland to eastern Victoria (Fig. 
9
).
